Here’s my hack to ripen avocados quicker. Bury unripe avocados in rice or place in a brown paper bag and store in a cool dark place like your pantry. Avocados produce ethylene gas, a plant hormone that triggers the ripening process. The rice or paper bag should trap the ethylene, holding it closer to the fruit and helping it ripen faster. Credit @myhealthydish

Watermelon Mint Sorbet! 🍉🌱
For those HOT days that are coming! It’s extremely refreshing, NO SUGAR ADDED, and a few ingredients only. 

🍉WATERMELON MINT SORBET:
🍉1/2 watermelon, cut into cubes and frozen
🍉A bit coconut water
🍉Juice of half lemon
🍉Handful of fresh mint 
👉🏽 Blend everything until a sorbet consistency. Add more coconut water if needed to help it. 
👍🏽You need a strong blender or use a food processor. 

By @tatytable

FERMENTED BLUEBERRY CHIA PUDDING. Really easy, really good GUT FOOD. By @panaceas_pantry 

Make sure to Save, Like, and Share 😘
 

Here’s the basic recipe:

1 cup frozen organic blueberries 
1 1/2 cups almond milk 
1/2 cup coconut yoghurt 
1/2 cup chia seeds

1. Blend together the berries and milk, then add to a large (very clean) glass jar along with chia seeds and yoghurt . It’s best in you use a jar with an airtight lid but it’s just not as easy to film 😆). Whisk together.

2. Ferment for approximately 12 hours, but note this can take longer. To asses when it’s ready look for all those bubbles (watch the reels again) and taste the pudding- it shouldn’t be sweet, and should be rangy and a bit fizzy.

3. Store in the fridge. To serve, top with whatever you fancy! I did raspberries, nut butter etc.

- 2 tbsp maple syrup

With Summer just around the corner I wanted to give you some tips on picking the perfect ripe watermelon. Dry weathering spots and vein like webbing are indicators of a sweet watermelon the spots are where the sugar has been seeping out of the fruit. The field spot should be creamy and yellow not white. Give it a good tap the sound should be hollow meaning it has more water. Lastly pick the heavy one for its size because it has more water content. #watermelon #watermelonsugar #watermelonjuice #howtopickawatermelon #healthyfood #fruithacks #eatarainbow #healthysnacks #healthysnackideas #naturescandy

node.text:
Blueberry Lemon Fluff 🫐🍋 Maybe we should call these bowls “breakfast ice cream”? 😛 by @fivesechealth 

Since I looove blueberry & lemon mug cake.. why not try and make a 🫐🍋 nice cream! It turned out SO GOOD. Refreshing lemony flavor, beautiful blueberry color, ice cream like flavor from 🍌, and a nice vanilla flavor from vanilla protein. This will be my summer go-to breakfast. I hope you’ll like this one too 😍

RECIPE (1 or 2 servings)
3 ripe frozen bananas
1/2 cup frozen blueberries
2 tbsp vanilla protein 
Zest and juice from 1/2 lemon
1/2 cup plant milk

Add all ingredients to a high speed blender. If you don’t have a tamper to push with, use a food processor! Mix until creamy and smooth. I topped mine with blueberries, walnuts and tahini.. because lemon and tahini is a match in heaven ✨
.
.
